    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix configuration mismatch issue in loader initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe shared library loader in the OAI codebase had inconsistent initialization state tracking that could lead to configuration mismatches between protocol layers. This issue manifested when the loader was initialized multiple times or when some fields were initialized but others were not.\n\nThe problem was caused by:\n1. `loader_init()` not being idempotent - it could cause memory leaks if called multiple times\n2. The initialization check in `load_module_version_shlib()` only checking `shlibpath` rather than the complete initialization state\n3. No proper state tracking to know if the loader was properly initialized\n\nUnder certain conditions, this could cause segmentation faults when trying to access uninitialized loader structures or incorrect behavior when loading shared libraries.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/load_module_shlib.c`: \n  * Made `loader_init()` idempotent by checking if already initialized\n  * Changed initialization check from `shlibpath` to `shlibs` allocation\n  * Properly initialize global `loader_data` structure to zero\n  * Enhanced `loader_reset()` to completely reset all state fields\n"
}